-- Manchester City Makes Record Bid for Barcelona's Alves, Sunday Mirror Says
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-13T12:11:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/manchester-city-makes-record-bid-for-barcelona-s-alves-sunday-mirror-says.html

          
          
             Manchester City has made a British
record 40 million-pound ($58.2 million) bid for Barcelona
fullback Daniel Alves and wants to sign his teammate Yaya Toure,
the Sunday Mirror reported.  
 Barcelona rejected the bid for Alves, although the 28-year-
old wants the opportunity to talk to City because he feels
promises have been broken over his contract, the newspaper said,
without citing anyone.  
